		{
			dependencies: ["2A2B25F44A4AE27B"]
			description: [
				"&7The main allure of Hex Casting is drawing pretty pictures in the grid because you don't have the slightest clue of what you're doing.&r"
				""
				"&d&lThe Basics&r&r"
				""
				"You can start this process by seeking out your nearest Amethyst Geode. Sometimes, breaking the Amethyst there will yield Charged Amethyst, which you'll need to craft the staff."
				""
				"Right-clicking with the staff will open a dot grid of sorts, where you can click and drag to create shapes. The shapes you create correspond to certain commands. "
				""
				"The rotation of the shape doesn't matter, but the angular direction (clockwise or counterclockwise) does."
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"&d&lSpellcasting"
				"To quote from the Hex Notebook:"
				""
				"• Patterns will execute..."
				"• Actions, which manipulate..."
				"• The Stack, which is a list of…."
				"• Iotas, which are simply"
				"units of information."
				""
				"That's a lot of stuff, but I'll elaborate. A pattern is basically any shape you can draw in the hex grid, even if it turns red and produces a bunch of garbage."
				""
				"An action is something caused by one of the shapes turning blue. Invalid patterns turn red and create garbage data on the Stack."
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"&d&lIotas"
				"Now, let's learn about the Stack and Iotas. These are the systems Hex Casting uses to store data, and this may be familiar if you've dabbled in programming before."
				""
				"An iota is a unit of data. Types include:"
				"• numbers, like 5.2"
				"• vectors (coordinates in the world), like [10, 64, -30]"
				"• booleans: true or false"
				"• entities: players or mobs"
				"• patterns: stored for advanced spells"
				"• lists: groups of other iotas"
				""
				"A stack is a temporary list of iotas used during a Hex. Actions manipulate the top (most recently added element) of the Stack."
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"&d&lMedia"
				"Let's not get ahead of ourselves. We still have a major factor to consider, one that almost every magic mod features: mana -- or media for hex casters."
				""
				"Every time you use an action, it consumes media. In Mincemeat 2, Amethyst Dust is the only item you need to cast spells, just make sure you have a good amount of it. If you run out before finishing your spell, it gets cancelled."
				""
				"&d&lRange"
				"Up to 30 blocks from your position. However, if you have a reference to an entity, it works at any distance."
			]
			icon: "hexcasting:staff/oak"
			id: "173A561DF4516DC0"
			rewards: [{
				count: 7
				id: "60E812642C820549"
				item: "lightmanscurrency:coin_iron"
				type: "item"
			}]
			shape: "hexagon"
			size: 1.5d
			subtitle: "Wait, I Wasn't Expecting Computer Science, I Want To Go Home"
