		{
			dependencies: ["173A561DF4516DC0"]
			description: [
				"The Stack is a core part of hex casting (and computer science as a whole). We can use a stack of plates as an analogy."
				""
				"The last item that gets added to the stack is the first one you can interact with. This principle is called \"LIFO\" (last in, first out). "
				""
				"&d&lStack operations:"
				"- Push: add an iota to the top of the stack."
				"- Pop: remove the top iota."
				"- Peek: examine or modify the top iota, but don't remove it."
				""
				"Many actions involve themselves with the Stack, which is why it's good to know how it works.."
				"- After processing, actions may push new iotas onto the stack."
				"  &oMind's Reflection pushes your entity iota.&r"
				"- Most actions pop iotas from the top of the stack to use as inputs."
				"  &oCompass Purification pops an entity iota and pushes its location vector."
				"- Some actions rearrange or duplicate the top iotas."
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"Here are some specific examples of how some actions might change your stack:"
				""
				"&dMind's Reflection"
				"Stack: [ ] --> [Caster Entity]"
				""
				"&dJester's Gambit"
				"&oPops the top 2 iotas, then pushes them in reverse order."
				"Stack: [A, B] --> [B, A]"
				""
				"&dGemini Decomposition"
				"&oPeeks the top iota, then pushes a copy."
				"Stack: [X] --> [X, X]"
			]
			icon: "beautify:bookstack"
			id: "2878EB75598EB9F3"
			subtitle: "Storing Data"
			tasks: [{
				id: "1887C19527D180A0"
				title: "Stack"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			x: -3.5d
			y: 1.0d
		}
