		{
			dependencies: ["18E1A2415EA939F2"]
			description: [
				"Through theurgy, you can also turn one material into another. The three types of transformation are:"
				""
				"- Reformation: the Sulfur changes, but not the type or tier"
				"- Transmutation: the type changes, but not the tier"
				"- Exaltation: the tier changes, but not the type"
				""
				"These practices build upon each other to create a powerful tool in your arsenal."
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"Since Sulfur is too mundane to be transformed directly, we'll need to make it into niter. No, neither of these are referring to the ores you find underground."
				""
				"There is a key difference between Sulfur and Niter: each material has a unique Sulfur, while Niter is instead sorted into broad categories. This allows it to be easily manipulated."
				""
				"For example, if you have a Precious Metal Niter, you can turn it into the Sulfur for any Precious Metal, then follow the steps in the Sulfur quest to turn it into a material you can use for other things."
				""
				"Keep that in mind for now, but the next quest doesn't concern Niter."
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"Now that you've passed Introduction to Alchemy, we can get to the fun part. You're going to build something called a Reformation Array."
				""
				"First, obtain a Target Pedestal, which will hold the sulfur you want more of."
				""
				"Then obtain a Result Pedestal, which will hold the duplicated sulfur."
				""
				"Next, obtain at least one Source Pedestal, will hold the sulfur you want to be converted into what's on the Target."
				""
				"Place the pedestals close to each other. There is no specific structure you need to build with them."
				""
				"Lastly, get a Sulfuric Flux Emitter, which supplies the energy this conversion needs. Make sure the emitter is linked to the other pedestals by right clicking it."
			]
