		{
			dependencies: ["31982B9D7EEA70B5"]
			description: [
				"For now, the Runic Workbench is going to be the main way of using your newly collected souls. It allows you to infuse souls into mundane items, transforming them into something entirely new."
				""
				"Runewood is a type of wood suitable for spirit magic. You can find it in plains and forests."
				""
				"Make yourself a Runic Workbench and surround it with Item Stands or Item Pedestals as you see fit - just make sure they're within 4 blocks of the workbench."
				""
				"You should start by crafting a Hex Ash, as this is an inexpensive and widely used material during infusion."
				""
				"See the next page for a diagram on how to read JEI infusion recipes."
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"{image:kubejs:item/malum_ritual width:262 height:333 align:center fit:true}"
				""
				"&c1:&r Necessary spirit. Right click the Workbench while holding this."
				""
				"&c2:&r The reagent. Place this upon the Workbench."
				""
				"&c3:&r The extra items. Place these upon the Item Pedestals or Holders."
				""
				"&c4:&r What you will get when the process is finished."
			]
